Malawian President Lazarus Chakwera arrives in Kenya for a three-day state visit. [Courtesy]  Malawian President Lazarus Chakwera has arrived in the country ahead of the Mashujaa Day celebrations tomorrow.  President Chakwera will be in the country for a three-day state visit and is also the Guest of Honor in tomorrow’s national celebrations.  Before departing for Kenya, Chakwera took to his official Twitter account to announce his visit, saying that bi-lateral talks between the two heads of state were one of the reasons for his visit.  “I am leaving for Kenya today at the invitation of my dear brother and friend President Uhuru Kenyatta. I will hold bilateral talks with him for the benefit of our people. I have also been honoured as Chief Guest at this year’s Mashujaa Day Celebrations for tomorrow.  Villains became heroes who should never be forgotten   Man, 67 treks fourth time to Mashujaa fete  Eyes on president as he hosts succession front-runners  Brace for traffic, Kenha says ahead of Mashujaa Day fete in Kirinyaga Chakwera arrived this evening in the company of First Lady Monica Chakwera ahead of tomorrow’s celebrations.  Together with his delegation, they were officially received at State House, Nairobi, by Defence Cabinet Secretary Eugene Wamalwa and his ICT counterpart Joe Mucheru.  This year’s Mashujaa Day Celebrations, marked annually on October 20, will be held at Wang’uru Stadium in Kirinyaga with only 2, 000 guests invited out of the possible 15. 000 (the stadium's capacity).   HOUSE OF CARDS: Is the State secretly engineering plot to have a compromise candidate succeed Uhuru?  Zaidi ya wafanyabiashara 300 kunufaika Kirinyaga, Mrundiko wa Kesi | MBIU YA KTN (Sehemu ya Pili)  Coffee farmers from Kirinyaga county set to benefit from value-addition machines By Lynn Kolongei | 18 seconds ago By Moses Nyamori | 4 hours ago By Grace Ng'ang'a | 4 hours ago By Roselyne Obala | 6 hours ago